overview: Vitamin D3 seems to lower blood pressure. There is mounting evidence that low levels are associated with diabetes type 1, muscle aches and pains, and, possibly more serious, cancers of the breast, colon, prostate, ovaries, esophagus, and lymphatic system. Vitamin D3 tablets should be at the top of your daily supplement regimen if you're trying to lower your risk of diabetes, heart attacks, rheumatoid arthritis, or multiple sclerosis. For better medication, always consult with your doctor.
